---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import heroPhoto from '../assets/about-hero-placeholder.svg';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Tanya Zakus, UX/UI Designer"
  description="UX/UI designer with 6+ years building humanist AI experiences and complex SaaS platforms. Open to full-time roles and freelance projects."
>

  <article class="max-w-[760px] mx-auto px-[var(--spacing-lg)] pt-[var(--spacing-2xl)] pb-[var(--spacing-4xl)]">

    {/* Block 1 — Hero photo (D-03). Full-width within the 760px content column.
        PLACEHOLDER: replace `src/assets/about-hero-placeholder.svg` with a real photo (16:9 or 3:2, .webp/.jpg/.png).
        Astro's <Image> component is used for WebP optimization + responsive srcset (D-03).
        Pattern copied verbatim from src/pages/projects/[id].astro:70-81. */}
    <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-[var(--color-secondary)] mb-[var(--spacing-2xl)]">
      <Image
        src={heroPhoto}
        alt="Tanya Zakus, portrait"
        format="webp"
        widths={[760, 1520]}
        sizes="(min-width: 760px) 760px, calc(100vw - 3rem)"
        class="w-full h-auto block"
      />
    </div>

    {/* Block 2 — "Now" availability eyebrow + hero headline + intro paragraphs (D-05 confident; D-06 eyebrow; D-04 1-2 sentences).
        Eyebrow uses the homepage variant: text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.08em] (matches src/pages/index.astro:26). */}
    <header>
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.08em] font-normal text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
        Now — Open to full-time &amp; freelance
      </p>

      <h1 class="mt-[var(--spacing-md)] text-[clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4.5rem)] leading-[1.05] text-[var(--color-text-primary)] max-w-[20ch]">
        Tanya Zakus, UX/UI designer for humanist AI products and complex SaaS.
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-[var(--spacing-lg)] text-[20px] leading-[30px] text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-[600px]">
        I&apos;ve spent six years designing the kind of software people use every day at work — B2B platforms, CRMs, and AI tools where clarity is the whole product. I care about the small details that make a system feel calm to use.
      </p>
    </header>

    {/* Block 3 — How I Work (D-07: title-case + medium-weight + body color; D-05 warm body). */}
    <section class="mt-[var(--spacing-3xl)]">
      <h2 class="text-[28px] md:text-[32px] font-medium text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-[var(--spacing-md)]">
        How I work
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[18px] leading-[1.625] text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-[600px]">
        I start by listening — to users, to support tickets, to the engineers who&apos;ll have to build it. Most design problems are clarity problems wearing a costume, so I look for the smallest change that makes the most expensive thing easier.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-[var(--spacing-md)] text-[18px] leading-[1.625] text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-[600px]">
        I work best with teams that ship in small slices, talk to their users often, and treat design and engineering as one conversation rather than a handoff.
      </p>
    </section>

    {/* Block 4 — Beyond Work (D-07; D-05 warm body; D-08 placeholder personality copy). */}
    <section class="mt-[var(--spacing-3xl)]">
      <h2 class="text-[28px] md:text-[32px] font-medium text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-[var(--spacing-md)]">
        Beyond work
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[18px] leading-[1.625] text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-[600px]">
        Outside of design, I&apos;m usually cooking something I&apos;ve never made before, walking long routes through new neighborhoods, or reading anything written by someone who really cares about their craft.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-[var(--spacing-md)] text-[18px] leading-[1.625] text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-[600px]">
        Lately I&apos;ve been curious about how small studios run — the ones that stay small on purpose.
      </p>
    </section>

  </article>

</BaseLayout>
